ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Started a fight
Hit someone with the idea of seriously hurting them
Gone out at night when your parents told you that you couldnt go
Taken something from a store without paying for it
Thrown objects such as rocks or bottles at cars or people
Broken or destroyed somebody elses things just for fun
Ran away from home and stayed overnight
How many times have you been picked up by the police, but not charged?
Broken into a house, store, school, or other building without the owner's permission
Taken something that didnt belong to you, like other kids clothes or lunches, or money from your parents without their knowing it
Have you ever tried cigarette smoking, even one or two puffs?
How old were you when you smoked a whole cigarette for the first time?
Notes: 0 = I have never smoked a whole cigarette; 1 = 8 years old or younger; 2 = 9 or 10 years old; 3 = 11 or 12 years old; 4 = 13 or 14 years old; 5 = 15 or 16 years old; 6 = 17 years old or older; 999 = Legitimate Skip; 7= 13 years or older

ElementDescription: During the past 30 days, on how many days did you smoke cigarettes on school property?
Notes: 0 = 0 days; 1 = 1 or 2 days; 2 = 3 to 5 days; 3 = 6 to 9 days; 4 = 10 to 19 days; 5 = 20 to 29 days; 6 = All 30 days; 999 = Legitimate Skip

ElementDescription: During the past 30 days, on the days you smoked, how many cigarettes did you smoke per day?
Notes: 0 = I did not smoke cigarettes during the past 30 days; 1 = Less than 1 cigarette per day; 2 = 1 cigarette per day; 3 = 2 to 5 cigarettes per day; 4 = 6 to 10 cigarettes per day; 5 = 11 to 20 cigarettes per day; 6 = More than 20 cigarettes per day; 999 = Legitimate Skip

ElementDescription: During the past 30 days, how did you usually get your own cigarettes?
Notes: 1 = I bought them in a store (convenience, supermarket, discount store, gas station); 2 = Vending machine; 3 = I gave someone else money to buy them for me; 4 = I borrowed (or bummed) them from someone else; 5 = A person 18 years or older gave them to me; 6 = I took them from a store or family member; 7 = I got them some other way; 999 = LEGITIMATE SKIP

ElementDescription: Has there ever been a period in your life when you smoked cigarettes every day for at least 30 days? PX030601_Cigarette_Smoking_Everyday_1Month
During the past 30 days, on how many days did you use chewing tobacco, snuff, or dip on school property?
Notes: 0 = 0 days; 1 = 1 or 2 days; 2 = 3 to 5 days; 3 = 6 to 9 days; 4 = 10 to 19 days; 5 = 20 to 29 days; 6 = All 30 days

ElementDescription: Have you ever had a drink of alcohol, other than a few sips?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 98= Do not know; 99= Refused

ElementDescription: How old were you when you had your first drink of alcohol other than a few sips?
Notes: 0 = I have never had a drink of alcohol other than a few sips; 1 = 8 years old or younger; 2 = 9 or 10 years old; 3 = 11 or 12 years old; 4 = 13 or 14 years old; 5 = 15 or 16 years old; 6 = 17 years old or older; 999 = Legitimate Skip; 7= 13 years old or older

ElementDescription: 8. Marijuana?
How old were you when you tried marijuana for the first time?
Notes: 0 = I have never tried marijuana; 1 = 8 years old or younger; 2 = 9 or 10 years old; 3 = 11 or 12 years old; 4 = 13 or 14 years old; 5 = 15 or 16 years old; 6 = 17 years old or older; 999 = Legitimate Skip;  7= 13 years old or older

ElementDescription: Cocaine
Ever carried a weapon?
Have you ever been in a physical fight?

Delinquent Behavior Total

Notes: (mean of DQ_1, DQ_2, DQ_3, DQ_4, DQ_5, DQ_6, DQ_7, DQ_8, DQ_9, DQ_10)
